  newsList:
  - header: Fans at a concert
    readHeader: Fans at a concert
    text: plenty of people at cool new artists concert. The artist know as DJ blueberry
      shot was believed to be a bad pick for the local concert, but turns out not!
      Around 17 people showed up at the concert wich was 17times higher than expected
    writer: Thomas Thomanson
    ID: 0
  - header: Heat wave
    readHeader: Heat wave
    text: All time highs in the tempature department, we could have prevented this!
      Climate change keeps destroying our nature and making everyday life harder.
      Its getting so bad that 13 people have died due to heat.
    writer: Jenny Moonrounder
    ID: 1
  - header: Leader of the Future Party In Jail!
    readHeader: <link="c"><u>Leader of the Future Party In Jail!</u></link>
    text: After the long, public trial comes to a close, leader of the Future party,
      Ms Grau, finds herself in jail for her crimes. "This'll set our party back
      years in terms of popularity" says a Future party representative (anonymously).
      The trial was . The accuser and leader of the People's Party, Mr Pikimusta,
      says "Truly despicable, what that woman did. She's not alone on this, either.I
      promise you her husband played a large part in this! His turn in the spotlight
      of justice too shall come soon. The Future party isn't innocent either!". None
      of what Mr Pikimusta says has been proven or disproven quite yet. Only time
      and new evidence will tell who Mr Pikimusta and his lawyers look to shine a
      light on next.
    writer: Ash Slate
    ID: 1
  - header: Suspicious Activity at Government Weapons Storages
    readHeader: <link="d"><u>Suspicious Activity at Government Weapons Storages</u></link>
    text: Hooded figures have been spotted around strategic army buildings. These
      individuals are said to be clad in dark green hoodies that shroud their faces.
      The army has refused to comment on the issue so far.
    writer: Gainsboro - alias
    ID: 1
